What's prefered?

``` javascript
const x = [{
  y: 'foo',
  z: 'bar',
}, {
  y: 'foo',
  z: 'bar',
}]
```

or

``` javascript
const x = [
  {
    y: 'foo',
    z: 'bar',
  },
  {
    y: 'foo',
    z: 'bar',
  },
]
```

This rules https://github.com/airbnb/javascript#jquery--find say:

```
// bad
$('.sidebar').find('ul').hide();

// good
$('.sidebar ul').hide();
```

but if using id selector it should be:

```
// bad (i mean it not good enough)
$('#sidebar ul').hide();

// this is best
$('#sidebar').find('ul').hide();
```

due to jquery performance https://learn.jquery.com/performance/optimize-selectors/#id-based-selectors
